Horses! <br>
&gt; <br>
Just like the transportation we use in the real world, horses range widely in cost and speed, from a relatively affordable 8400pp Chevy to the 105,000pp Porche. They are summoned from a riding whip, and cannot exist at the same time as any pet or familiar. There are 4 color choices, brown, tan, white and black, 4 whip types, rope, leather, silk and chain, and sizes vary depending on your race. The summoning whips are no drop, so you'll have to buy your own pony, no Christmas gifts, but they are not lore, so if you're really rich you can buy a horse to match each outfit.  You can cast on horseback, but not while riding, and no mean monsters are going to slay your horse unless they kill you first. The two of you are one!  The animations are beautiful, and as a horse person in real life, I'm particularly impressed by the little touches. It takes a while for your horse to hit running speed, it will walk a few steps, trot a few steps, then speed up and race like the wind. The view is very realistic in first person view, so targetting might be a bit of an issue, and the different sizes mean the different racial heights are even more noticeable. The sound of hoofbeats as you race across the world will make you believe you can feel the wind in your hair. <br>
<br>
I'm going to have to start having foragers save me carrots. My pony deserves the very best! <br>
<br>
Available for sale at any reputable stable are sixteen types of bridle, these are split into four categories Rope, Leather, Silk and Chain (These correspond to the speed of the horses, with Rope being roughly equivalent to the speed of Journeyman's Boots and Chain being slightly slower than Spirit of The Cheetah.). The colour of each bridle corresponds to the colour of the horse Tan, Brown, White and Black. The prices can range from 10,000pp being the cheapest to 113,750pp for the most expensive (Depending on you faction with <br>
the merchants.). <br>
<br>
Now once you have purchased a bridle you will need to place it one of your main inventory slots and summon your magical steed by right clicking on the bridle. After a few seconds your mount will arrive and you will be placed upon his or her back. If you no longer require the services of your fine <br>
steed you only need click the icon in your buff window and you mount will disappear to be called again when you need him. <br>
<br>
Horses can only be summoned while outside. <br>
<br>
While riding a horse you can perform all the actions you could under normal circumstances e.g. Spell casting. <br>
<br>
Before you say what is the point of owning a horse when you can quest for Journeyman's Boots or buy a Spirit of the Wolf potion ? Well they are a status symbol for the rich and famous and look wonderful. <br>
